.planning/review/REVIEW-codex.md:21:- MEDIUM, CORRECTNESS/provenance, `ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs:1845`: mzPeak output records `MS:1000544` “Conversion to mzML,” which is false for direct RAW→mzPeak output. Concrete fix: use a mzPeak/TRFP conversion processing method and wire numpress processing IDs consistently into array metadata.
.planning/review/REVIEW-codex.md:23:- MEDIUM, TEST COVERAGE, `ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakWriterTests.cs:39`: most writer tests force `MzPeakPointLayout = true`, so the default numpress output path is under-tested. Concrete fix: run the same schema/value gates over point, lossless chunk, and numpress default.
.planning/review/REVIEW-codex.md:25:- MEDIUM, TEST COVERAGE, `ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakDifferentialTests.cs:193`: the differential gate compares reference `--no-numpress` to our `--point`, skipping the actual default and much centroid coverage. Concrete fix: add pyarrow-driven differential checks against `small.unpacked`, `small.chunked`, and `small.numpress` for schemas, footers, and decoded values.
.planning/review/REVIEW-codex.md:27:- LOW, MAINTAINABILITY, `ThermoRawFileParser/Writer/MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs:21`: 2006-line writer mixes RAW extraction, precursor inference, Parquet schema/levels, streaming, chromatograms, index JSON, and provenance. Concrete fix: split into metadata builders, facet writers, index builder, CV/param helpers, and scan extraction without changing verified behavior.
.planning/review/REVIEW-codex.md:29:- LOW, BLOAT/leakage, `tools/e2e/compare_mzpeak.py:58`: strip process/research comments: also `ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakWriterTests.cs:1524`, `:1735`, `:1738`, `:1756`, `ThermoRawFileParser/ThermoRawFileParserTest/MzPeakChunkTests.cs:441`, `:673`, `:982`. Concrete fix: replace with neutral technical comments or delete.
.planning/review/REVIEW-codex-final.err:14:Final confirmation re-review after fixes. The mzPeak code was fixed per .planning/review/SYNTHESIS.md: Wave 1 (correctness — nullable absent values, complete spectrum/scan schema matching small.numpress.mzpeak, provenance MS:1000530, empty-spectrum rows, per-facet array_index), Wave 2 (cleanup/dead-code/CURIE-table/comment-strip/coverage), Wave 3 (decomposed the 2079-line MzPeakSpectrumWriter into 290-line orchestrator + Writer/MzPeak/*.cs). Read SYNTHESIS.md + the current Writer/MzPeak/*.cs + MzPeakSpectrumWriter.cs. Verify with python3.11+pyarrow vs refs/mzPeak/small.numpress.mzpeak: (1) spectrum=19/scan=12 columns match name+order; (2) absent values are null not 0 (MS1 rows have null precursor/selected_ion; unknown polarity null); (3) the refactor preserved behavior (validator concerns). Confirm the prior BLOCKERs (spectrum/scan missing cols, nullability) are RESOLVED, and list any NEW issues the refactor introduced. Note the documented deviations (intensity-SLOF out of scope; Arrow field-metadata not emittable by Parquet.Net — conveyed via footer) are acceptable. End with VERDICT: CLEAN / FIXES-NEEDED.
